{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_romeo_ver02/data/sn84026749/100492659/1907101301/0458.xml":{"full_text":"TA TEN EN I NH I IE EEE EE EE EE III...\nNEW YORK\u2014STOCKS, BONDS, AND MONEY\u2014WASHINGTON|\n6\n\nSERIOUS SLUMPS\nIN THE NEW YORK\nSECURITY LISI\nFirst Holders of Stocks Gave\nUp the Fight and Dump\nTheir Shares,\niE\n\nIndustrial Situation Is Bad.\nForeign Liquidation a\nSerious Factor.\ni\n20g\nNEW YORK, Oct. 12 -The past week\nhas basen full of discouragement for the\nmen who are carrying stocks. They\nhave been forced to witness the gradual\nmelting away of values for \u2018many\nmontas, until, in the opinion of many,\nthe bottom was close at hand. The\nbears had reached a stage where they\nwere sated with profits, and apparently\ninclined to the belief that it was about\ntime to put on the brakes and slow\ndown, as there seemed 10 be a cessation\nof offerings, and, In some instances,\nthey had been trimmed good and proper\nin their short selling.\n\n\ndt 3\n\n\n3\nj\n\n\n\n\n\nJ\n\n\n\n\na. Co\nSAE, A abe\nxt. Nor.\n\n111. Cent Wh,\nN\nInter. Metro 8%\nIn. Met, Pr.. 9\nC mT\nThis was especially true of their at\ntempted coup in selling down Canadian\nPacific, for the moment they attempted\nto cover they were brought up with a\nround turn, no stock being offered, and\na sharp advance making their covering.\nKan. C. So 20\nKan. C. So. pfd. 50\nes Neirranns 9\nMan. Elev 5%\nyey Geng oe\nr hah\nM, K. T...... 28\nk 2 S\nMes Ks c T. ptd. 64\nMo. Pac ..ocui... 88\nMoreover, the low prices did not seem\nto bring out much liquidation, lead\ning to the opinion that stocks were\nstrongly held, and that it would take\nsomething new in the way of depressing\ninfluences to turn tha tide and force out\nreach liauidation. LJ\nFNAL Big es 63 ane\nNat'l Lead.\n\n\n69\n\n\"he payment of an extra dividend ol\n1% per cent on Great Northern preferred\nwas some:hing of a bull influence, giv\ning the market a stronger opening.\nindeed, there were some sharp gains in\nthe opening of the week. It was a sur\nprise to the Street that the Great North\nern directors should make a distribution\nat a time when rallroads were supposing\nto be husbanding their resources, and\nit is questionable whether or not it had\na good influence.\np\n\n\n\n\n\n2\nI\n\n392%\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u2014p\n\n\ni\nFor some little time it was thought\nthat Northern Pacific officials might\nfollow the example of the Great North\nern directors and make an extra distri\nbution, but they did not, and the mar\nket atruck a snag quickly after this\nfact became known and kept on the\ndown grade most of the week, relieved\nnow and then, temporarily by the cov\nering of the shorts who never hesitated\nto put out a new line after once getting\nin under cover.\n\n1 1\n1\n\n\n1\nprobably\n\n\n\u201cAsk him\ni\n\n\n\nr 1\n\nThe chief influence was th\u00e9 industrial\nsituation, admittedly bad. The copper\nmarket is in an abnormal slump and\nevery bit of unfavorable news publish\ned concerning it but stiffens the back\nbones of the users of the metals and\n\u2018makes them independent about buying,\nas they are continually holding off for\nlower prices.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRB MARKE\n\nSmelting and refining has led in a de\ncline, the sales on Friday being 98,000\nshares. Some unfavorable news is ex\npected. There were rumors of Gov\nernment investigation, and also a story\nof a serious decline In the price of sil\nver,\n\n\ni\n\n\n\n\ni\n\nForeign liquidation was in evidence\nall through the list, some of the strong\nest stocks being dumped by continental\nholders, with Amsterdam sending over\norders with great freedom.\n\n\n\n1 EI\nPri.\n\n\n10.88\n10.96\nThe banks of .New York discrimninated\nagainst industrial shares and added an\nother blow to the weakness. Then, too,\nthere were reports of financial trouble\nin the Northwest and West.\n10 og\n10.3\u00a2\nETT\n\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014\u2014mmmwk\n\n\nThe combined effect of the mnltitude\nof bear rumors was to bring on a new\nwave of liquidation, to disgust stock\nholders who during all the slump had\nstood pat with thelr shares locked away\nand paid for. But the melting away of\nvalues was too much for thelr nerves,\nand many not only unloaded and got\nout, but some unloaded and stayed in,\nturning rampant bears and playing to\nget even on that side of the market.\n\na AR\n\n2%\n#1 11 46%\n16% 16% 15\n31 Jac\n3 3 3% de\n430 430 435\ni 1\n8\noo\n\nfy\n\nThe long-continued slump has been an\nawful strain on the insiders, as the\nStreet terms the big men who control\nthe various groups of railroads. New\nlow records have been made in nearly\neverything during the past week, and\nnothing has been safe from the raids\nof the bear element. Their Canadian\nPacific experience did mot make them\nquit attacking high-grade rails, and they\nhave been operating in the Pacifics, in\nPennsylvania, New York Central, Read\ning, and other leaders. The low-priced\nshares have found little favor in this\nmarket, and have heen permitted to sag\nand sag again, going in thelr own sweet\nway toward a lower level.\n\n1\n\no\n\n4 i\n\nSe\n\n\n\n\n\nNor was there support to many of\nthe safe dividend e\u00a2arners. The insiders\nconld not give the support and the in\nvesting public was not in\u2018 evidence.\nStocks have reached a point where there\nare admittedly many rare bargains on\nthe counter, but with the tendency al\nways to lower range, the men with con\nfidence and nerve enough to buy confi\ndently aweited lower figures\nThe unseitled condition of the (United\nStates Steel shares did as much as any\nthing else to unsettle confidence and\nto burn up stoeks. It is stated that but\nfew orders are being booked, and that\na shutdown of many of the corpora\ntian\u2019s mille is only a question of a few\nweeks cr months at the longest. Admit\ntedly the corporation is fixed to stand\nan era of depression, but when 90,000\nshares of the common stock and neariy\n40,000 shares of the 7 per cent preferrea\nare sold on one day, as on Friday, it is\nall too plain that the movement is not\nall due to short selling. There must\nhave buen heavy liquidation of holdings\ncarried down from 108 and between that\nrice and the opening price of Friday.\n1.\nBanks have passed through the week\nwith a fairly steady money market, but\nthe crop movement is heavy, and there\nis little chance for a change toward\neasier money in the near future.\nIn any event, speculation is to be dis\ncouraged, while those who have\nand cash enough to buy securitic {ran\nnot go far. wrong In taking on= gh\nStrengthens the Opening.\nres\nSmelting Very Weak.\n\nStrain on Holders of Stock.\nSteel Situation Bad.\n{Quotations furnished by A. O. Brown\nCo., Munsey Building: Members New York\nStock Exchange.\nEa eatin es rn Ra\nMatWitNay VSNL La\n\nI\nTatal aalegs vestearday ST AOD\ny h. Low.\nAllis Chal, Pr. ish Oh 10% 15% a\nAm. Beet Sugar. 16 16 10 10 W'%\nAmal. Cop....... 2% Mi Sih 3 ai\nAC EEHEE SI BL 8\nm ot \u201cass p\nAm. Loco......... BH. MWg BOY\nAm. Loce,, pfd.. 94 94 4 9\nAm. Smelt. i% o% [LE\nAm. Smelt. pra, 2 uN S1% 92 Wa\nAm. Sugar.. 103 104% 102% 10434 1045\nAm: Tob., pfd.. 4 yr yy\nAm. Woolen...... 1 15% 16 17%\nAnaconda 82% 2 Ne 33\nAtchison 8215 X2 813g 82%\nAtctitson, pid... $s 30s 85% $4 8815\nAt. Coast L...... 0g 70%: 70% lia\nBethlehem Stuel. LE Be AR\nBalto. Ohio.... $5% 85% 84% 85% 86\nBig Four.. 41 40 40% \u00a5o4\nCan. Pacific......1 150 157% 159 15%\nCent. Lr... 1 13% 13% 13% 14%\n\u201cent. Lr. Pr...... 76 iw T6, Wy\nhes. Ohio.... 2 25 Ct 30\nh. G. Wesi, 7 iL\nC. GW. \u201cB\". 11% 1% 10% 10 11%\nC., M.. St. P.14% 114% 114% 114% 1158;\nCol. Buel......... Hi 15 16 1o%\nCk BO vss snrss 19% 19% 19% dy\nC. 4.3a8, (N. X.). 3 S1% a 91 J\nCorn Prod........ BH 1 10% 11%;\nCorn Prod., pfd. 60% KOI 603, 60% WiLL\nDo fin. a, 1, M0 0, i\n\nanne\nEE a p\u2014\u2014\u2014\n\n\n\n\noS iL\ni\nv A, 7 w\nR pfd. 63% Soa on 34 54\nDistiniers C7 46 46 4 HY e%\nEre .......54- 18 18% 18 18 IN\n