t of Columbia 3.65's. 114%.\nPhilippine 4's, 106%.\nLONDON MARKET\nLONDON, Oct. 12\u2014Consols today\nwere unchanged at 82 1-16 for money\nand $2 13-16 for account. Canadian Pa\ncific closed 13% lower at 163, Grand\nTrunk was unchanged at 21%, Anaconda\nwas 3 lower at \u00a36%.\nMoney was in small supply and quiet\ndemand. Discounts were firm. \u2018The Bank\nof England today sold \u00a350,000 in French\ngold.\n\n\nOn the stock exchange trading fin\nished the week unfavorab.y. Consois\n2nd other first-class securi ies eased on\nthe monetary outlook. Anticipation of\na better bank statement and moderate\ncovering caused a slight improvement,\nbut the market reacted and closed weak.\nDiamond shares, especially premiers,\nwere firm on a rumor that an agreement\nhad been reached between the corpora\ntions.\nForeigners were quietly steady.\nCHICAGO GRAIN A\u2122wv PRUVYISIONS.\nSaturday; Oct. Fri.\nWheat A H';'h. Low. Rosaclose\nDec 10% 104% 106% i04%\ncay. 111 109% His 110%\nyn\u2014\nDec 81 631 61 6314 6ilg\nMay ai 63% \u00a96l% 63% Gly\nOats\u2014\nN\npay Lil hy 563% bil 26%\ni 1550 16.02 1580 15.00 15.92\nNEW YORK COFFEE MARKET.\n3] RES\nDec.......\ngauss\nwwwe\nD475\nSpee\nG&A\npeeve\ndens\nOpen,\n6.\n6.\n8.\n6.\nSaturday, Oct. Bis\nMay....\nSly. ciuvan\nMar.....\nALMOST AS IMNTORTANT.\n\u201c1 supvose,\u201d' observed the curious\npassenger, \u2018you know the exact loca\ntion of all the dangerous rocks along\nthie coast.\u201d\n\u201cNo, sir,\u201d answered the pllot, \u201cbut I\nknow the exact location of all the safe\noT\nWASHINGTON STOCKS\nUNDER PRESSURE\nSeveral Drops That Indicated\nForced Liquidation of\nWeak Accounts.\nIt was not to be expected taat matters\nin the local securities market during the\npast week would be specially encourag\ning or that there would be any reason\nto expect any bullish sentiment. Condi\ntions in Wall Strect were so unsatisfac\ntory that it would have required a very\noptimistic person *o believe that Wash\nington could e\u00a2scupe from the storm\nwithout feeling at least the edge of it.\nThat prices held so well was due large\nly to the fact that for some weeks past\nthere has been but little specuiative\nbuying, except in one or two instances,\nand the market wes therefore in 8 most\nexcellent conditior. to =.thstand the\nshock.' Trkat it was a shock goes with\nont saving\nCapital Traction 5's\nWash, Ry. and Elec\nMISCELLANEOUS BONDS.\nNort, end Wash\nWashington Market 5's 15\nWashington Market i's, 1947\nPUBLIC UTILITY\nads ah fl a\na at dhe\nshock.\u2019 Trat it was a shock goes with\nout saying.\nProphecies Gone Wrong.\nne was more or less of a surpirse that\nthe turn of the market should be so un\nexpectedly bad, as conservative bank\ners and others have been predicting that\nfollowing the 1st of October and the\ncoming of the fall season there would be\na return of prosperity, afid that the\nmoney market having passed through\nthe crop-moving period would loosen\nup, and that easier money with all its\nattendant good results would prevail\nThat such has not been the case, but\nthat the week closed with a gloomier\nview than ever 's one of tne cases\nshowing how the prophets were mis\ntaken.\nNor. and Wash. Steamboat\nWashington Gas\nGeorgetown Gas.\nChes. and Pot. Telephone\nHow Washington Suffered.\nTurning mcre particularly\u2019 to the 03\nures of the week on the Washington\nstock board, it app-oars that Gas, Wash\nington Railway, praferre\u00a2 and common,\nwere the most affected, Gas stock\nshowing a loss of 5 points and a closing\nevel lower, while the preferred raii\nway dropped from 7% to 68, and the\ncommon to 32, both prices being the low\nest that have existed for three years, and\nreturning almost te the figures that\nobtained before the movement in them\nwhich carried them up to high levels.\nThere was also some remarkable scil\ning of Greene Carnanea and Mitchell\nMining, which, however, was not sur\nprising, in view of the weakness of the\ncopper metal. Lanston was also weak,\nwhile Mergenthale: showed unexpected\nstrength and heid almost to the best\nprices throughout.\nTRUST COMPANY STO\nloan and Trust\nSAVINGS FANK STOCKS\nFIRE INSURANCE ST\nISCELLANEOUS STOCK\nBright Spots Also.\nSales on bank and trust stocks were\nfew, and in each case there was slight\nevidence of weakness. In the cac- of\nthe stock of the mew United States\nTrust Company, thwe was a good ad\nvance, which put It above par aud\n\u2018held Ite there throughout the entire\nweek. The same good condition pre\nt:ajled through the bund marked, and\nto the surprise of everyone there was\n\u00abspectacular advance in those Of the\nCapital Traction Company, which had\nremained so long in status que that the\nsudden jump was the cause of ruch\nTrans. and Storags....\nwonderment. Altogether, it was a week\nfilled with much to keep interest awakh\nened.\nGreene Copper Figures.\nAbout twenty stockholders, represent\ning the minority interest of the Greene\nConsolidated Copper Company, who had\nexpected to attend the annual\nmeeting that was to have been\nheld Wednesday in New York, wanted\nto know avhy they had not received any\ndividends since the merger with the\n'Greene-Cananea Company. On July 31\n\u2018the Greene Consdl:lated Company had\n$7,000,000 in its treasury, but no divi\ndends were d because the company\nhad not ized any profits from the\nsale of copper.\nMetro. Bank..\nIn the recent stock market demorall\nzation no group of stocks has suffered\n\u2018anything ke the loss which has been\nsustained mm the so-called Cole-Ryan\ngroup. From the high point of this year\nto the low nt the aggregate stock\nmarket shrin in five of their prop\nerties has exceeded $15\u00a7, 000,000. hirty\nper cent of this loss is represented by\nthe decline of $45,000,000 in GreeneCan\nBhaar=the last of the Cole-Ryan floia\nEmployer (to his clerk)\u2014Is it true that\nwhen the clock strikes 8 u put 4-wn\nvour pen and go, even if you are in tue\nmiddle of a word?\nClerk\u2014Ce